シの音で終わる動詞にはやはり同じ規則が用いられます。

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:15.140
Rub your hands, John, I said. John at once rubbed his hands.

00:01:15.140 --> 00:01:19.480
Change your seat, John, I said.

00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:24.180
John at once changed his seat.

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:32.280
The sound of the verb る is like the sound of the verb change.

00:01:32.280 --> 00:01:38.820
The verb る is like the sound of the verb ド.

00:01:38.820 --> 00:01:53.220
The rule of adding the sound of ド to the sound of the verb change is applied to the case of a vowel or a vowel.

00:01:53.220 --> 00:01:54.420
For example,

00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:58.420
Open the door, John, I said.

00:01:58.420 --> 00:02:01.620
John at once opened the door.

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:05.420
Enter the room, John, I said.

00:02:05.420 --> 00:02:08.420
John at once entered the room.

00:02:08.420 --> 00:02:27.620
However, the verb ッ with the sound of 立ちつて and 立ちつて with the sound of ド is added to the case of ッ.

00:02:27.620 --> 00:02:29.220
For example,

00:02:29.220 --> 00:02:32.220
Plant a tree, John, I said.

00:02:32.220 --> 00:02:36.220
John at once planted the tree.

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:40.820
Unfold the branches, John, I said.

00:02:40.820 --> 00:02:46.020
John at once unfolded the branches.

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:55.820
Plant, planted, unfold, unfolded.

00:02:56.020 --> 00:03:02.220
The above shows only the case of the past,

00:03:02.220 --> 00:03:13.220
Please remember that the way to make the past tense of the rules is exactly the same as the past.

